SENATE RESOLUTION 402
By Yager
A RESOLUTION to commend Nicole Herschberger for exemplary
service as a Senate Republican Caucus Press
Clerk.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this body is pleased to recognize certain persons
who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Nicole Herschberger is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in
her role as a Senate Republican Caucus Press Clerk; Ms. Herschberger's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for Senator Ken Yager, the legislators she assisted, and the Senate
Republican Caucus as a whole; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Herschberger achieved academic success by earning a Bachelor of
Business Administration degree in Accounting from Belmont University in 2020; and
WHEREAS, prior to her time with the Tennessee legislature, Nicole Herschberger
served as a campaign coordinator and an assistant press secretary for a candidate for
Pennsylvania Lieutenant Governor and as a podcast producer for The Sarah McAbee Show;
and
WHEREAS, Ms. Herschberger was a regional manager and spokesperson for TPUSA
Faith, fostering relationships with local pastors and community leaders and supporting ministry
leaders and elected officials with educational resources; she also served as a strategist for
EPIC, in which role she implemented publicity, communication, and social media strategies for
faith-based and conservative political book, film, and nonprofit campaigns; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government, Ms. Herschberger brought her many abilities and singular
SR0402
017615
